description:
The scripts required to reproduce the analysis in&nbsp;&quot;Toxin-antitoxin RNA pairs safeguard CRISPR-Cas systems&quot;.&nbsp; 

 There are two pipelines, one is used to map&nbsp;the small RNA sequencing reads to the  creTA  operon, and the other is used to search for  creTA  analogs in the sequences flanking&nbsp;bacterial or archaeal&nbsp; cas6  genes.&nbsp;&nbsp;For each pipeline, there are two perl scripts&nbsp;involved. Please read the &#39;Pipelines&#39; file for more information. 

 &nbsp;

